Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8

The VHDL compiler generates an illegal LPN when the condition of an
if-statement contains a "less than or equal to" or a "greater than or
equal to" operator.

One example is located in
/home/ming/zhangz/nobackup/research/lpn/noc2by2_livelock_free/r_PE_11.vhd.
The condition one_flit(0 downto 0) <= "1" does not compile correctly.
You should compile the top-level file "top_r_PE_11.vhd" in the same
directory.

The second example is in
/home/ming/zhangz/nobackup/research/lpn/noc2by2_livelock_free/r_PE_01.vhd.
The temporarily modified condition one_flit(1 downto 1) >= "0" will
generate an illegal LPN. Similarly, you should compile its top-level
file "top_r_PE_01.vhd" in the same directory.

